From forys@cs.utah.edu  Tue Feb  7 21:23:02 1989
Date: Tue, 7 Feb 89 22:21:49 -0700
From: forys@cs.utah.edu (Jeff Forys)
Subject: I just send a slightly dated version of sendmail/collect.c
Index: 	usr.lib/sendmail/src/collect.c 4.3BSD
Apparently-To: 4bsd-bugs@BERKELEY.EDU

Description:
	The copy of collect.c I just sent you was slightly dated and
	consequently, had "the last bug" still in it.  You see, all
	our RCS dir's are linked to one machine and I didnt co(1) this
	version on the machine I was sending mail on and, and... *sigh*.

Repeat-By:
	As a result, the label "readerr:" is too low, resulting in a
	left-open file descriptor and there is problem with lines
	longer than MAXFIELD (this bug was actually in 5.61).

Fix:
	Obviously, I should be more careful... here's the `right' version.

